This course aims at enabling non-technical students to develop a comprehensive understanding on the energy crisis and environmental issues. Upon completion of the course, students should have achieved the following outcomes:

1. identify the seriousness of energy crisis in 21st century. They will recognize the energy options we have and compare their impacts on the environment;
2. analyze the scientific debates on the nature, causes, and consequences of global warming. Students will illustrate the complexity of environmental issues our society is currently facing;
3. recognize essential components to develop a green society;
4. evaluate the local and global development from a comprehensive point of view.

This course is built around the fundamental understanding of basic principles, techniques, and applications of AI. The cornerstone of this course involves evaluation of AI systems in our daily lives and exploring potential solutions with AI and machine learning technologies. Upon successful completion of the course, students shall be able to achieve the following outcomes:

1. explain the basic concepts and major elements of today's AI technology;
2. understand and use the basic terminology of AI;
3. describe the basic types of tasks that an AI system can accomplish;
4. explain the operation of major applications of AI;
5. suggest possible new use cases of AI;
6. explain the role of data in AI;
7. describe the workflow for AI application development.

